# =====================================================================
#  Ayah uses one .env file per package (not a single root .env). This
#  keeps each package runnable on its own and matches the num-ninjas
#  layout.
#
#  Copy each example to a real .env in the same folder:
#
#    cp packages/database/.env.example  packages/database/.env
#    cp apps/telegram/.env.example      apps/telegram/.env
#
#  packages/database/.env  -> DATABASE_URL (Prisma CLI + seed)
#  apps/telegram/.env      -> BOT_TOKEN, DATABASE_URL, TZ_NAME, ...
#
#  See each file for what every variable means.
# =====================================================================
